<br>
Focus items and crits affect EER, GSS and all the new stuf in EXACTLY the same ratio, so don't get all caught up in bringing that into the discussion.<br>
<br>
It's all about damage, mana, cast time, range, recast time and recourse.  And its about having a new spells at higher levels that make you even bother getting them.<br>
<br>
Draught of fire ruled over Conflagration.  Ice Spear is clearly better than Ice Comet.  Lure of Flame is better than Enticement.  If I am looking at using my level 65 big fire gun versus my level 60 big fire gun...it should be a no brainer.  What we see them floating to us is very muddy.<br>
<br>
Sure, if I am opening up on a solo mob, I want the biggest damage possible.  But, with SoS's ratio, no way....because I know it's not just this mob, but the next one and the next to rack up the experience, therefore making mana efficiency VERY important.<br>
<br>
This SoS spell (as we perceive it) is bunk.  For the pain of 5 levels of advancement, I do NOT want to face a crappier mana efficiency and a recourse.  I can just as easily cast GSS twice and avoid the wasted nuke and healer mana.  Pointless spell...but it ain't over yet. <p>Kazzap Allahandra 60 Wizard<BR>
Iskendar Woundtempest 53 Warrior<BR><BR>
