<br>
The recourse isn't much of a concern.  ~Most~ wizards by the time they hit 60 have their epic.  And so long as the recourse is a DD, it's nothing to cry over.  And if you think 300 hp is alot of damage, well, it's not.  Just keep a stack of peridots with you and hit yourself with spellshield before the attack is called.<br>
<br>
The mana:damage ratio is, well, shit.  It's pre-Kunark mana damage ratio, and anyone who was a wizard back then knew how bad that sucked.<br>
<br>
SoS will be, at best, a -very- situational spell.  What situation?<br>
<br>
Think Sontalak/Klandicar.  Think mobs with 5 second's between AE's.  For you more old school people who were in VP before Velious opened, think Hoshkar.  Think mobs where agro management isn't as important as doing a shitload of damage in under 16 seconds is.<br>
<br>
Personally?  I'm dissapointed they didn't include another AE snare, or a better root that y'know, lasts more then .2 seconds so we can at least ghetto crowd control, or more AE nukes.  The thing I gather from that is that PoP is not gonna be a place you group for XP.  You're gonna dungeon crawl with an entire guild, and that's how you build PoP levels.<br>
<br>
But that's just my thoughts, and I thought Willow was a great movie.  Go figure. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=35824><img src="http://perfectflaw.ath.cx/images/eq/yaspsucks.gif" border=0></a><br>
